        "locator": "Sec. 1 and Sec. 3",
        "text": "The paper names a trust-region concern and an off-policy concern, argues that fixed clipping conflates them, and asks the current batch to measure behavior-policy mismatch through normalized effective sample size.",
        "source_refs": ["feynrl-paper:sec1", "feynrl-paper:sec3"]
      },
      {
        "locator": "Eq. 11 and Eq. 12",
        "text": "Equation 11 defines normalized ESS from per-token policy ratios. Equation 12 uses e_B in the score-function weight and the off-policy regularizer of Policy-on Policy-off Policy Optimization.",
        "source_refs": ["feynrl-paper:eq11", "feynrl-paper:eq12"]
      },
      {
        "locator": "Sec. 4 and Table 7",
        "text": "The experiments test clipping factor, sampling temperature, and BF16 Train plus FP8 Rollout. Table 7 reports exact held-out pass@1 values, including the late precision-mismatch result.",
        "source_refs": ["feynrl-paper:sec4", "feynrl-paper:table7"]
      }
